Police Operatives from Oleh Division in Isoko South Local Government Area of Delta State have arrested three suspected armed robbers in Sagbama, Bayelsa State. The suspects who are all indigenes of Igbide Community are George Akporie, Prosper Asaeta and Eziekel Stephen. The Police also recovered one locally-made gun from the suspects. The suspects were arrested after they allegedly shot and snatched a Qlink Motorcycle from a thirty-three-year-old man. The incident reportedly happened on March 5th, 2021 between Olomoro and Ehwen Communities. The victim was taken to Olomro General Hospital where he was treated and discharged while the Police initiated an investigation. However, the victim spotted one of the hoodlums who attacked him on 23/01/2022 around Sagbama, Bayelsa State and immediately alerted the Police Command. It was gathered that the Delta State Commissioner of Police, CP Ari Muhammed Ali directed that operatives from Oleh Division proceed to Bayelsa State for a discreet investigation to arrest the suspects. The Delta State Police Command led by CP Ari Muhammed Ali confirmed the report in a statement signed by the Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe. He said, â€œThe suspects will be charged to court upon completion of investigations.